This program implements a simple calculator using lex and yacc coding.

Requirements:
lex/flex to compile and execute the '.l' file
yacc to compile and execute the '.y. file
gcc to compile and execute the '.c' file


Step of execution:
1) Install Lex and YACC in Ubuntu via the terminal using the commands:
     sudo apt-get update
     sudo apt-get install flex
     sudo apt-get install bison
     sudo apt-get install bison flex

2) The 'lexcode.l' and 'yaccfile.y' are the files we will be executing.

3) In terminal(in the directory) use the commands:
     yacc -d yaccfile.y     
     lex lexfile.l
     gcc y.tab.c
     ./a.out

5) When prompted, input an an expression to calculate Eg. 5+2*3
